It was a convergence of fun as thousands of kids converged at the Landmark Event Centre, Victoria Island, Lagos, for the launch of MTN Nigeria’s mPulse, which is targeted at Nigerian tweens and teens ranging from age nine to 16. The kids played physical games like life-sized Ludo, monopoly as well as virtual games.The children also expressed their creativity with plasticine just as wunderkinds like Waris Kareem of Waspa Art who showed off immense artistic  skills. Also, there was a lot to eat as cupcakes, pizza, sandwiches and other yummy delights were available.